        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 7:18PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 718 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Belleville, or near Romulus, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Livonia, Taylor, Romulus, Canton, Dearborn, Northville, Belleville,
Westland, Dearborn Heights, Garden City, Inkster, Ferndale, Wayne,
Hazel Park, Plymouth, Redford, and Northwest Detroit.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
southeastern Michigan.</instruction>
